this one.   \n", "author": "FlyinHeadlock", "created": 1771462343481, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "nerfherder", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "In the early 90's I was on the USS Lincoln. Some NGO got on us for using plastic bags for food trash. We started using paper but lined the paper bag with plastic bags. It was impossible to haul food trash in paper bags.  ", "last_comment_created": 1771465051458, "content": "<p>My point is the winner in all this was the paper bag company. I don't know how they get rid of trash today but that paper bag company made a fortune, all over bullshit. We still had to use plastic. These bags were 3 1/2 feet high, super heavy. Impossible without plastic. I have many more stories of this NGO grifting BS but I will start with this one.</p>\n", "score_down": 1, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 4, "score_up": 39, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "2024285032882311668", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASFqlKCMb", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 25, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8430979, "raw_content": "", "author": "PiratePatriotParrot", "created": 1771470527458, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "LORDFALCONE", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "twitter.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASFqlKCMb.png"